modName: UNP UNPB UNPB-BBP CBBEv3 Conversion of the Tsun Female Armor by Fallen Judge
summary: Converts the CBBE Female Tsun armor by Fallen Judge to UNP and UNPB, and modifies the CBBE version slightly.  It also makes some minor changes to the original .ESP file.
descriptionHtml:
Main Files:

UNP, UNPB and UNPB conversion of the Female Tsun armor by FallenJudge, as well as some modifications the original CBBE armor.


Optional Files:

NSFW-Topless versions of the UNP, UNPB and CBBEv3 armor.  Also included are NSFW-Topless BBP conversions of all three armors.


With the help of both FallenJudge and Acolyte598, There is now an Add-On that completes a fully playable version of the Tsun armor.  It includes ALL the fixes and updates, so just let it overwrite the ESP and \"1st Person\" meshes and you should be good-to-go!
Files You\'ll Need:
1. FallenJudge\'s Original \"Tsun Female Armor\" Mod
2. The Female Conversion of your choice
3. The \"Add-On\"

The \"v1 Update\" ONLY includes the 1st person fixes and a new ESP that points to the new meshes.  Unlike the \"Add-On,\" it DOES NOT include the bracers, circlet or male version of the armor.


I\'ve also added  a \"Light\" version of the .ESP for the Tsun Armor, since I\'ve seen requests for it.  All I\'ve changed is the .ESP, so you still need to download the \"v1\" update to get the 1st person meshes.
The new Armor Ratings are: 28 for the Cuirass and 7 for the Boots.
The new Weights are: 8 for the Cuirass and 2 for the Boots.
To install the new .ESP, just drop the Data folder into your Skyrim directory and over-write the existing .ESP file.  I\'ll upload a \"Light\" version of the \"Add-On\" ESP soon.

To install the new Armor Meshes:
First, you need the original mod by FallenJudge - \"CBBE Tsun FemaleArmor\" http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/17298

Then, you need to drop the Armor mod of your choice into your \"Skyrim\" directory, and over-write the meshes when prompted.

To install the \"v1 Updated .ESP and new Meshes:\"
Drop the new \"Data\" folder into the Skyrim directory, and over-write the original \"FJ_TsunArmor.esp\" file.  The new one has the same name, so you shouldn\'t have to do anything else to activate it.

To install the \"v1b Light Armor Variant .ESP:\"
You need to have the \"v1 Update\" installed already (see above.)  Drop the NEW \"Data\" folder into your Skyrim directory, and over-write the \"FJ_TsunArmor.esp\" file.  Again, the new one has the same name, so nothing special needs to be done to activate it.  In the future, a \"Light Version .esp\" will be included, as an option, with ALL updates.

To install the \"Add-On:\"
Drop the \"Data\" file into your \"Skyrim\" directory and let it over-write the 1st Person meshes and the ESP.  Still the same name, so nothing new needs to be done to activate it.


The \"NSFW\" versions of the armor were added at the prompting of my \"lady love,\"  who always wonders why, when she loots the body of a bare-chested guy, they all seem to have some sort of \"bra-top,\" just in case they lose their armor to a woman in battle...So these versions are by ReflexShooter and AmberR... ;-)

A quick note:
If you use the console command \"Help Tsun\" to get the armor, FallenJudge has the femal armor and female boots listed as \"Tsun Armor\" and \"Tsun Boots.\"  \"Beth\" has the MALE versions listed as \"Tsun\'s Armor\" and \"Tsun\'s Boots.\"  If you enter the \"Beth\" numbers, you\'ll wind up with the wrong armor and no boots.  If you use the \"Add-On,\"  the new \"Circlet/Helmet\" and \"Bracers\" use the same naming conventions.

Remember that these files STILL require the ORIGINAL \"FallenJudge\" files as a base for all the changes, so install THAT mod first.

And check out the \"Silver Armor\" mod by Acolyte598.  It\'s a different \"take\" on making a free-standing version of the Tsun armor.
